Issue: "AssistFirewall_UprBoundKSV_M_str.SV" and " AssistFirewall_HiFreqKSV_M_str.LPF.SV " output variables are going out of range.

Analysis:

a) AssistFirewall_UprBoundKSV_M_str.SV output variable get updated in " LPF_OpUpdate_f32_m" macro at src line no.732 as mentioned below:

UprBoundFilt_MtrNm_T_f32 = LPF_OpUpdate_f32_m(UprBound_MtrNm_T_f32, &AssistFirewall_UprBoundKSV_M_str);

In LPF_OpUpdate_f32_m macro,

LPF.SV = ((data - LPF.SV) * LPF.K) + LPF.SV

Range of AssistFirewall_UprBoundKSV_M_str.SV = -8.8 to 8.8
AssistFirewall_UprBoundKSV_M_str.K = 0.001255848 to 0.715390457

So at one test vector in which overflow exists
data=15.995(get updated at src line 722)
LPF.SV=8
LPF.K=0.6
so finally the value of AssistFirewall_UprBoundKSV_M_str.SV coming as 12.79970703.


b) AssistFirewall_HiFreqKSV_M_str.LPF.SV output variable get updated in " HPF_OpUpdate_f32_m" macro at src line no.701 as mentioned below:

HiFreqInput_MtrNm_T_f32 =HPF_OpUpdate_f32_m(SumInput_MtrNm_T_f32, &AssistFirewall_HiFreqKSV_M_str);

Range of AssistFirewall_HiFreqKSV_M_str.LPF.SV= -8.8 to 8.8
AssistFirewall_HiFreqKSV_M_str.LPF.K = 0.001255848 to 0.715390457 and
AssistFirewall_HiFreqKSV_M_str.LPF.CF= 1.000628633 to 2.095379522



In HPF_OpUpdate_f32_m macro,

HPF.LPF.SV = LPF_OpUpdate_f32_m(data, HPF.LPF)

And in LPF_OpUpdate_f32_m macro,
LPF.SV = ((data - LPF.SV) * LPF.K) + LPF.SV

So at one test vector in which overflow exists
data=26.4(get updated at src line 698)
LPF.SV=8.8
LPF.K= 0.715390457
so finally AssistFirewall_HiFreqKSV_M_str.LPF.SV is coming as 21.390 which is going out of range.

Note: In UTP test type for both out of range variables are created and UTP is attached for your reference.

Similarly, for AssistFirewall_HiFreqKSV_M_str.LPF.SV is - 21.3908720372859 to 21.3908720372859 and if we use this in input value then again out of range issue is observed.
